<TITLE> 3-year old raped </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 7 (bdnews24.com)  A girl, barely three years old, has been raped in Uttarkhan, Dhaka. She was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital's One Stop Crisis Centre in a critical condition on Wednesday morning. The mother of the child, who works as a domestic help at a house in Ambagan Barabagh area, said her daughter was raped Tuesday afternoon. She told bdnews24.com that she took her daughter to the house where she worked. She found her daughter covered in blood at a room in a house next to the one where she was working. The girl was initially taken to a local clinic and shifted to DMCH on Tuesday night. The child was shifted to the One Stop Crisis Centre Wednesday morning. Duty doctor Salahuddin Mollah told bdnews24.com that bleeding had stopped after operation but her condition is still critical. "The child is still in a trauma." The child's uncle Md Khairul Islam said they could not identify the criminal yet. Uttarkhan police chief Md Nazmul Imam said they had already initiated investigation to identify and arrest the criminal. The child's guardians had told him that they would file a case, he said. 
